and resurrection?

00:37:45.144 --> 00:37:49.110 align:middle line:84%
Could the Bible be an
actual historical source

00:37:49.110 --> 00:37:53.956 align:middle line:84%
that had preserved some of the
Neanderthal fundamental wisdom,

00:37:53.956 --> 00:37:57.455 align:middle line:84%
preserving it for
us in a veiled form?

00:37:57.455 --> 00:38:05.375 align:middle line:90%


00:38:05.375 --> 00:38:09.990 align:middle line:84%
Ralph Solecki, an archaeologist
who worked at the Smithsonian

00:38:09.990 --> 00:38:15.266 align:middle line:84%
Institution, went to do an
excavation in northern Iraq

00:38:15.266 --> 00:38:19.320 align:middle line:90%
in a cave called Shanidar.

00:38:19.320 --> 00:38:22.010 align:middle line:84%
What he discovered he
published in a book

00:38:22.010 --> 00:38:25.060 align:middle line:84%
called "Shanidar: The
First Flower People."

00:38:25.060 --> 00:38:28.580 align:middle line:84%
In the cave of Shanidar,
Solecki discovered

00:38:28.580 --> 00:38:35.010 align:middle line:84%
nine Neanderthal skeletons, the
most ever found in one cave.

00:38:35.010 --> 00:38:39.040 align:middle line:10%
During the excavations that
took many years to uncover,

00:38:39.040 --> 00:38:43.040 align:middle line:10%
Solecki discovered
something extraordinary

00:38:43.040 --> 00:38:47.200 align:middle line:10%
that changed completely the
perception of Neanderthal up

00:38:47.200 --> 00:38:48.732 align:middle line:10%
to that point.

00:38:48.732 --> 00:38:51.790 align:middle line:90%
This was 1971.

00:38:51.790 --> 00:38:56.290 align:middle line:84%
What he discovered was
a burial with flowers.

00:38:56.290 --> 00:38:58.730 align:middle line:84%
The Neanderthals had
buried their dead

00:38:58.730 --> 00:39:03.990 align:middle line:84%
with seasonal flowers that
also had medicinal purposes.

00:39:03.990 --> 00:39:07.000 align:middle line:84%
This was quite
shocking to discover,

00:39:07.000 --> 00:39:10.470 align:middle line:84%
the compassion of these
people and the fact

00:39:10.470 --> 00:39:13.340 align:middle line:84%
that they believe
in an afterlife.

00:39:13.340 --> 00:39:16.640 align:middle line:84%
The flowers found
in the Shanidar cave

00:39:16.640 --> 00:39:19.560 align:middle line:90%
are found in Bucegi.

00:39:19.560 --> 00:39:23.650 align:middle line:84%
It was a spring burial
with flowers that

00:39:23.650 --> 00:39:27.670 align:middle line:90%
were white, violet, and yellow.

00:39:27.670 --> 00:39:31.940 align:middle line:84%
In his excavations, Solecki
discovered other things

00:39:31.940 --> 00:39:36.480 align:middle line:84%
that changed our
perception of Neanderthal.

00:39:36.480 --> 00:39:42.220 align:middle line:84%
He discovered the skeletons
of handicapped and old people,

00:39:42.220 --> 00:39:44.910 align:middle line:84%
so it meant that
the Neanderthal had

00:39:44.910 --> 00:39:48.590 align:middle line:84%
to take care of their
sick and their old.

00:39:48.590 --> 00:39:51.120 align:middle line:90%
Isn't that such a human touch?

00:39:51.120 --> 00:39:55.900 align:middle line:84%
Solecki called the
Neanderthals people

00:39:55.900 --> 00:39:58.840 align:middle line:90%
with such good characters.

00:39:58.840 --> 00:40:05.090 align:middle line:84%
We should be proud to have
them as our ancestors.

00:40:05.090 --> 00:40:07.880 align:middle line:84%
This is a far cry from
the view of Neanderthal

00:40:07.880 --> 00:40:10.820 align:middle line:84%
held for most of this
century, that they were

00:40:10.820 --> 00:40:13.570 align:middle line:90%
a brutal subspecies of humans.

00:40:13.570 --> 00:40:16.280 align:middle line:84%
In light of recent
evidence, Neanderthal

00:40:16.280 --> 00:40:19.540 align:middle line:84%
emerges shockingly
close to a modern human,

00:40:19.540 --> 00:40:23.100 align:middle line:84%
a sensitive, highly
intelligent creature

00:40:23.100 --> 00:40:26.161 align:middle line:84%
with a well-developed culture
and a well-developed sense

00:40:26.161 --> 00:40:26.961 align:middle line:90%
of self.

00:40:26.961 --> 00:40:30.420 align:middle line:90%


00:40:30.420 --> 00:40:34.280 align:middle line:84%
Like any good scientific
theory, Gooch's ideas

00:40:34.280 --> 00:40:36.910 align:middle line:84%
are subject to testing
and further exploration.

00:40:36.910 --> 00:40:44.450 align:middle line:90%


00:40:44.450 --> 00:40:47.890 align:middle line:10%
Two hours walking
distance from the Sphinx,

00:40:47.890 --> 00:40:51.720 align:middle line:10%
