00:58:54.760 --> 00:58:57.610 align:middle line:84%
But it's called the
Mechid, which loosely

00:58:57.610 --> 00:59:00.220 align:middle line:90%
translates as the church.

00:59:00.220 --> 00:59:03.890 align:middle line:84%
And this suggests right away
that there's something special

00:59:03.890 --> 00:59:05.370 align:middle line:90%
about this area.

00:59:05.370 --> 00:59:06.720 align:middle line:90%
What is the Mechid?

00:59:06.720 --> 00:59:11.630 align:middle line:84%
It's this incredible limestone
formation, huge formation,

00:59:11.630 --> 00:59:14.320 align:middle line:90%
incredibly symmetrical.

00:59:14.320 --> 00:59:20.270 align:middle line:84%
And it appears to me as if
it were a stage or a podium,

00:59:20.270 --> 00:59:22.730 align:middle line:90%
but of enormous scale.

00:59:22.730 --> 00:59:25.010 align:middle line:90%
At a scale-- I think of giants.

00:59:25.010 --> 00:59:26.830 align:middle line:90%
It's a huge scale.

00:59:26.830 --> 00:59:29.750 align:middle line:90%
And it's symmetrically arranged.

00:59:29.750 --> 00:59:31.610 align:middle line:90%
It itself is symmetrical.

00:59:31.610 --> 00:59:37.060 align:middle line:10%
And it sits in the little valley
area that forms, in my mind,

00:59:37.060 --> 00:59:39.220 align:middle line:10%
a natural amphitheater.

00:59:39.220 --> 00:59:44.060 align:middle line:10%
